The paper deals with the problem of Single Image Super Resolution (SISR) for large-scale images, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The authors propose a novel attentional SISR model using a generative adversarial network (GAN), which involves training a deep neural network (DNN) to generate high-resolution images from low-resolution inputs, a topic that falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a distributed algorithm to speed up training, which is a topic in parallel and distributed computing (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR).
